The paper deals with the problem of solving parity games, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The paper introduces and studies the concept of universal ordered trees, which is a topic in logic and automata theory. The paper also discusses the construction of separating automata, which is a topic in computational complexity. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
